file.title: AMM PART II-1285 - LIST OF EFFECTIVE AIRCRAFT

page.data: AIRCRAFT MAINTENANCE MANUAL LIST OF EFFECTIVE AIRCRAFT The Aircraft Maintenance Manual (AMM) has been prepared in accordance with Air Transport Association of America (ATA) Specification No. 100 - Revision 33. The basic issuance date of this Manual is September 30, 1999. Successive revisions affecting this Manual will be numbered sequentially (Rev. 1, 2, 3, etc.). This Manual is applicable to the aircraft listed in the table below. This table provides a cross-reference between marketing and certification designations. Table 1 - AIRCRAFT DESIGNATIONS Aircraft Marketing Designation Aircraft Certification Designation ERJ-135ER / RJ-135ER EMB-135ER ERJ-135LR / RJ-135LR EMB-135LR ERJ-145EU / RJ-145EU EMB-145EU ERJ-145MP / RJ-145MP EMB-145MP ERJ-145LR / RJ-145LR EMB-145LR ERJ-145EP / RJ-145EP EMB-145EP The effectivity cross-reference tabulation below contains the following columns: • Aircraft model – designation assigned by Embraer; • Customer aircraft number - effectivity used by Embraer to control the configuration for each customer; • Manufacturer serial number – this is the primary and unique identifier over the life cycle of the aircraft, marked on the nameplate located on the aircraft tail cone lower part. The manufacturer serial number can be used in this manual to specify differences between aircraft configurations. The manufacturer serial number is composed of the aircraft model designation code (145 for EMB-145) and a sequential number composed of three digits for serial numbers 001 through 800, and five digits for serial numbers 00801 and on. This sequential number indicates de production sequence of the aircraft of the same type. • Aircraft registration number - the number visible on the aircraft exterior, assigned by the respective government authority. NOTE: • EMB-145MK models are EMB-145MP models that have incorporated S.B. 145-00-0006. Effectivities ALL and MP are also applicable to EMB-145MK models. • After incorporation of S.B. 145-00-0007, an aircraft EMB-145MK becomes an EMB-145MP again.
